#: ../../language/error_codes/E0042.md:1
msgid "E0042"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0042.md:3
msgid "Warning name: `invalid_attribute`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0042.md:5
msgid "Invalid attribute."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0042.md:7
msgid ""
"This warning will be emitted when the program contain attribute "
"unrecognized by MoonBit, or the syntax of attribute has incorrect shape."
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0042.md:10
msgid "Erroneous example"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0042.md:11
msgid ""
"///| unrecognized attribute\n"
"#unrecognized\n"
"fn f() -> Unit {\n"
"\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"///| `#deprecated` can accept at most one message\n"
"#deprecated(\"multiple\", \"message\")\n"
"fn g() -> Unit {\n"
"\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0042.md:15
msgid "Suggestion"
msgstr ""

#: ../../language/error_codes/E0042.md:16
msgid ""
"Check if there is typo in the attribute declaration, and check the "
"document of the attribute for the arguments it accept. If you intend to "
"write a attribute for use by foreign tools, make sure the attribute's "
"name is `#xxx.yyy`, such as `#coverage.skip`, so that MoonBit will treat "
"it as a foreign attribute and ignore it."
msgstr ""

